    "pr_title": "fix(control-ui): harden Dashboard webchat reply menu",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nRepairs #92654, which implements the Dashboard / Control UI webchat right-click Reply workflow tracked by #16896.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe PR is useful and has green functional proof, but Copilot review left actionable merge blockers: preserve the native context menu when reply is unavailable, keep Escape dismissal registered until cleanup, avoid timestamp-generated reply IDs, build the custom menu without `innerHTML`, add menu focus/ARIA handling, escape Markdown sender labels before quote insertion, clear reply state only after a send is accepted, guard delayed listener registration after menu removal, and remove unrelated CSS focus/font-size churn.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers keep the intended right-click Reply flow without losing native context-menu behavior, leaking listeners, or sending malformed quote prefixes.\n\n## Evidence\n\nSource PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/92654 by @programmingWTF. Planned validation: `pnpm test ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` and `pnpm check:changed -- ui/src/ui/views/chat.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.ts ui/src/styles/chat/layout.css ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`.",
